**1. Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**

*   **Count & Layers:** The structure is composed of 20 blocks and has 3 layers.
*   **Spatial Relationships:**
    *   **Layer 1 (Bottom):** The base layer consists of two red arch blocks (blocks 2), and one horizontally oriented yellow block (block 10).
    *   **Layer 2 (Middle):**  One red arch block (block 1) and a yellow horizontally oriented block (block 9) are placed on the left side; two green blocks (blocks 5) are placed on top of the yellow and a single red block (block 2).
    *   **Layer 3 (Top):**  Two red blocks (block 1) on top of the yellow, and two green blocks (blocks 5) are placed on top of the yellow block and a single blue block (block 6), an orange trapezoid (block 15) block on top of the blue block.
